# `not-found.tsx` — invalid truth boundary

## Doctrine

```txt
not-found.tsx = invalid truth boundary
```

It means:

```txt
route exists
shell exists
but requested org / module / record is not valid truth
```

`not-found.tsx` is not a generic 404 page. It is the segment-level declaration that the **requested resource does not exist** while keeping the **operational shell intact**.

Docs: [Next.js — not-found.js](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/file-conventions/not-found)

---

## Afenda rule

```md
Use not-found.tsx to preserve operational continuity when a resource is missing.
The shell — sidebar, topbar, org context, navigation — must remain mounted.
```

---

## How it renders (docs-validated)

`not-found.tsx` renders **inside the parent layout** — it is wrapped by the same `layout.tsx` that wraps `page.tsx`. This means:

```txt
dashboard/not-found.tsx → rendered inside DashboardShell (sidebar intact)
admin/not-found.tsx     → rendered inside OrgAdminWorkbenchShell (sidebar intact)
operator/not-found.tsx  → rendered inside PlatformAdminShell (header + sidebar intact)
```

This is intentional. A 404 inside the dashboard should not destroy the shell — the user still has navigation, org context, and can recover. This is the GitHub-style behaviour: 404 inside operational continuity, not 404 that destroys the experience.

Component hierarchy:
```
layout → template → error → [loading wraps] → not-found / page
```

---

## Triggering `not-found()`

`notFound()` from `next/navigation` throws `NEXT_HTTP_ERROR_FALLBACK;404` and terminates rendering of the segment where it is thrown.

```tsx
import { notFound } from 'next/navigation'

// In a layout — triggers not-found.tsx for this segment
const identity = await fetchOrgWorkbenchIdentity(orgSession.organizationId)
if (!identity) notFound()

// In a page — triggers not-found.tsx for this segment
const record = await getContactById(id)
if (!record) notFound()
```

---

## Cannot receive `params` as props

`not-found.tsx` does **not** receive route params. To access dynamic segments (e.g. `orgSlug`):

- **Client Component** using `useParams()` from `next/navigation` — preferred when recovery links need dynamic values
- **Server Component** using `headers()` — for locale-aware content when no dynamic params are needed

```tsx
// dashboard/not-found.tsx — Client Component for orgSlug access
"use client"
import { useParams } from "next/navigation"
import { Link } from "#i18n/navigation"
import { Button } from "#components/ui/button"

export default function OrgDashboardNotFound() {
  const params = useParams<{ orgSlug: string }>()
  return (
    <div className="flex min-h-[40vh] flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 p-6 text-center">
      <div className="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <p className="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">404</p>
        <h1 className="text-lg font-medium text-foreground">Page not found</h1>
        <p className="max-w-md text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          The dashboard shell is still available — use the sidebar to navigate.
        </p>
      </div>
      {params?.orgSlug ? (
        <Button asChild variant="outline" size="sm">
          <Link href={`/o/${params.orgSlug}/dashboard`}>Back to dashboard</Link>
        </Button>
      ) : null}
    </div>
  )
}
```

---

## Correct use in Afenda

```txt
app/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/dashboard/not-found.tsx   ✓ dashboard org/module missing
app/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/admin/not-found.tsx        ✓ admin identity missing
app/[locale]/operator/not-found.tsx                 ✓ operator section missing
```

Use it for:

```txt
org identity not found (layout calls notFound())
record not found (page calls notFound())
module route invalid
admin resource missing
```

---

## Shell continuity requirement

When the route surface has a shell component:

| Surface     | Shell                    | not-found.tsx wraps in... |
| ----------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------- |
| Dashboard   | `DashboardShell`         | Auto (layout wraps)       |
| Admin       | `OrgAdminWorkbenchShell` | Auto (layout wraps)       |
| Operator    | `PlatformAdminShell`     | Must wrap explicitly      |

For **operator** pages: `PlatformAdminShell` is in each page, not in the layout. The `operator/not-found.tsx` must explicitly wrap in `PlatformAdminShell` to maintain the brand header and sidebar.

```tsx
// operator/not-found.tsx — explicit shell for continuity
import { PlatformAdminShell } from "#features/platform-admin"

export default function OperatorNotFound() {
  return (
    <PlatformAdminShell>
      <div className="...">...</div>
    </PlatformAdminShell>
  )
}
```

