## HTTP status and streaming (docs-validated)

> Next.js will return a 200 status for streamed responses and 404 for non-streamed responses, impacting SEO.

| Where `notFound()` is called                        | HTTP status |
| ---------------------------------------------------- | ----------- |
| In a **layout** — before any `await` or Suspense    | **404**     |
| In a **page** behind a `loading.tsx` Suspense       | **200**     |

**For public indexed routes** — call `notFound()` before any `await` or `<Suspense>` boundary:

```tsx
// CORRECT for public SEO pages — real 404 before streaming starts
const exists = await checkSlugExists(slug) // fast existence check
if (!exists) notFound()                    // fires before any Suspense

return <Suspense fallback={...}><PostContent slug={slug} /></Suspense>
```

**For private authenticated surfaces** (dashboard, admin, operator) — 200 vs 404 is invisible to users and SEO is irrelevant. Shell continuity takes priority.

---

## When NOT to add `not-found.tsx`

- Do not add a `not-found.tsx` to every nested segment speculatively
- For rare missing-record cases inside a page, use inline conditional rendering or `notFound()` without a dedicated not-found file (the parent segment's not-found will catch it)
- For known empty states (empty contact list, no knowledge chunks), use inline empty-state UI — not `notFound()`
